  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I think the logic to choose idle as the initial state is that the InstantSearch instance isn't yet started, so technically the first search isn't yet fired. You can use `results.__isArtificial` to work around this for now (will be `true` in the initial pre-load state).\n\nWhat do you change in the PR that addresses this? Happy to have a look and discuss to see what behaviour is more correct / less surprising.",
    "created_at": "2025-03-13T14:16:59Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/6607#issuecomment-2721424943",
