    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Thanks for the quick reply! The PR would do exactly that, check the `results.__isArtificial` property to check if the results aren't artificial. I had another implementation in mind, where there's another `hasReceivedResults` prop on the `SearchResultsApi` interface. You can see how it would be implemented [here](https://github.com/tharropoulos/instantsearch/commit/09508a10841663445789d1a5249ef1cefca5b89d).\n\nThe only thing I'm not stoked about currently, is that it feels a bit scary using internal variables inside client code, since there's no guarantee that the behavior will remain consistent as time goes on.\n\nAlso, just because I was checking the library out, there's a small change that could be beneficial for DX in regards to the dunder prefix (`__`) using tilde (`~`) prefix instead, since that will de-prioritize the property in autocomplete. Credits to [colinhacks](https://x.com/colinhacks/status/1816860780459073933).\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4d27a522-9d83-4a3d-bf68-67a5c869b6a2)",
